<br>
Seriously though, perhaps you are just blinded to the issue due to your obvious bleeding-heart, liberal approach to the inadvertant downgrades warriors have experienced.  Your constant analogies to big-business and how they are teh debil, and &quot;oh you big bullies are hoarding all the good stuff&quot; jealous type of attitude does rub me wrong; not that you care of course.  And lemme tell ya bud, it isn't just at 60 with end-game gear.  It is all levels.  Ya I'm 60 in a good guild, but by no means the top MT anymore.  So recently to get the missus to start playing I made a little SK twink.  I geared him up decently and off we went.  Through the past couple weeks of grouping, I've noticed a consistency.  No one seeks warriors out in low-mid level groups.  The shout for &quot;melee&quot; is usual.  But groups I've been in turn away warriors cuz I tank and keep aggro better than they can.  It isn't my weapons that make me aggro better, it's my spells with the taunt button I get to use with it.  A warrior in comparable gear might have a few more hps, but the AC would be the same and with my spells my damage output is probably close to theirs.  Keep building this up over another &lt;insert levels&gt; and that warrior is gonna be where we are at; frustrated and annoyed that he isn't actually the best at anything when he was supposed to be the best at ONE thing.<br>
